    "refcode_long": "Counsels on Sabbath School Work, p. 111.1 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Why is it that many seem to think that a responsible position exalts the man? Why do they become so self-sufficient when they are so utterly dependent upon the atoning Sacrifice? Why is there with some so great a want of tenderness, so little heart work? It is because those who are self-sufficient have not fallen upon the Rock and been broken. This is why there is so little trust in God, so little earnest, contrite repentance, so great a lack of fervent prayer. Well may the questions be put by every instructor: &ldquo;Have I received the Holy Ghost since I believed? Have I received Christ as my personal Saviour?&rdquo; Let these questions be solemnly answered.",
